{"id":22120,"title":"Unusual heart transplantation for iterative disinsertion of mitral prosthesis.","abstract":"Heart transplantation is the gold standard of care for end-stage heart failure, usually associated with an impairment of left ventricular systolic function. We describe a case of heart transplantation in a 58-year-old man with normal left ventricular systolic function, because of recurrent mitral prosthesis disinsertion after multiple reoperations for infective endocarditis. ","date":"2014-02-26","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24569335","annotations":[{"name":"Endocarditis","weight":0.821773,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocarditis"},{"name":"Heart failure","weight":0.793125,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_failure"},{"name":"Mitral valve","weight":0.735569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitral_valve"},{"name":"Infective endocarditis","weight":0.702422,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infective_endocarditis"},{"name":"Prosthesis","weight":0.70225,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosthesis"},{"name":"Ventricle (heart)","weight":0.655043,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ventricle_(heart)"},{"name":"Heart","weight":0.626514,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart"},{"name":"Organ transplantation","weight":0.607968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organ_transplantation"},{"name":"Heart transplantation","weight":0.571231,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_transplantation"},{"name":"Systole (medicine)","weight":0.55757,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systole_(medicine)"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.544856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Left ventricle","weight":0.523279,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Left_ventricle"},{"name":"Gold standard (te